---

<BaseLayout
  title="Crystal's Corner — Reviews, Hot Takes & Chevy Adventures | ChevyRoots"
  description="Crystal's Corner: Reviews, hot takes, Chevy adventures, and the unfiltered voice behind ChevyRoots. Run by a Chevy Girl."
  ogImage="/photos/crystal/crystal-silverado-zr2-hero.jpg"
>
  {/* ── HERO ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-hero">
    <div class="cc-hero-bg-stripe"></div>
    <div class="cc-hero-gold-bar"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cc-hero-inner">
        <div class="cc-hero-content">
          <div class="cc-hero-eyebrow">Crystal's Corner</div>
          <h1 class="cc-hero-title">Crystal's<br />Corner</h1>
          <p class="cc-hero-tagline">Run by a Chevy Girl</p>
          <p class="cc-hero-intro">
            Houston born. Virginia living. Chevy driving. This is where I talk about what I love — every Chevy I drive, every show I hit, every hot take I can't keep to myself.
          </p>
          <div class="cc-socials">
            <a href="https://tiktok.com/@chevyroots" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cc-social-pill">@chevyroots · TikTok</a>
            <a href="https://instagram.com/chevyroots" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cc-social-pill">@chevyroots · Instagram</a>
            <a href="https://youtube.com/@chevyroots" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cc-social-pill">ChevyRoots · YouTube</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cc-hero-photo-wrap">
          <div class="cc-hero-photo" role="img" aria-label="Photo of Crystal with her Silverado ZR2"></div>
          <p class="cc-hero-photo-caption">The Chevy girl behind all of this.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── LATEST FROM CRYSTAL ─────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section" aria-labelledby="latest-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// latest posts</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="latest-heading">Latest from Crystal</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">Reviews, hot takes, culture, and pure Chevy chaos — all from one girl with a lot of opinions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cc-cards-grid">
        {latestPosts.map((post) => (
          <article class="cc-card">
            <div class="cc-card-thumb" style={`background-image: url('${post.image}');`}>
              <span class={`cc-card-type cc-card-type-${post.typeClass}`}>{post.type}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cc-card-body">
              <h3 class="cc-card-title">{post.title}</h3>
              <p class="cc-card-preview">{post.preview}</p>
              <div class="cc-card-footer">
                <span class="cc-card-date">{post.date}</span>
                {post.status === 'live' ? (
                  <a href={post.anchor} class="cc-card-cta">Read it →</a>
                ) : (
                  <span class="cc-card-cta" style="opacity:0.4;">Stay tuned</span>
                )}
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── FIRST REVIEW: CAMARO ────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section" id="camaro-review" aria-labelledby="camaro-review-heading">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// first review — april 5, 2026</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="camaro-review-heading">Crystal's First Review</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">This is the first real piece of editorial content on ChevyRoots. Unfiltered, from the driver's seat.</p>
      </div>

      <article class="cc-first-review">
        <div class="cc-first-review-hero">
          <div class="cc-first-review-hero-meta">
            <span class="cc-first-review-badge">First Drive / Review</span>
            <span class="cc-first-review-date">April 5, 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cc-first-review-body">
          <h3 class="cc-first-review-title">I Rented a Camaro for a Day</h3>
          <p class="cc-first-review-subtitle">2024 Camaro SS — Rapid Blue — 6.2L V8 — One Very Good Day</p>

          <div class="cc-first-review-prose">
            <p>
              Let me set the scene. It's a Tuesday. I show up to the rental counter fully expecting to walk out with a beige Nissan Altima and go on with my life. Instead, the guy behind the desk says they're out of midsize sedans and asks if I'd be okay with — and I quote — "something a little sportier." Reader, it was a 2024 Camaro SS in <strong>Rapid Blue</strong>. I said yes before he finished the sentence.
            </p>
            <p>
              First impression the second you lay eyes on it in the lot: it's low. Like, <em>actually</em> low. Squatted, wide-shouldered, aggressive in a way that reads less "sports car" and more "I will absolutely do something your insurance doesn't cover." The Rapid Blue popped in the morning light — this deep metallic blue that shifts almost purple depending on the angle. I stood next to it for probably two minutes before I even got in.
            </p>
            <p>
              Then I started it. Oh. The V8 fires up with this deep, rumbly exhale — not a scream, not a bark, just a confident growl that says <em>I've been waiting</em>. Pulling out of the lot, I kept the windows down even though it was a little chilly because I needed to hear every single thing going on under that hood. First corner at normal speed and the steering already feels connected and direct in a way my daily just doesn't. It's communicating with you. You can feel the road.
            </p>
            <p>
              The best moment of the day came somewhere on a back highway with no one around. I got on it. Not stupid-fast, just — let it breathe. The exhaust opened up, the whole car flattened out, and for about ten seconds I completely understood why people build their lives around these things. It wasn't just speed. It was the whole experience: the sound, the pull, the way the seat is holding you while everything around you starts moving faster. That's the Camaro. It's theater and it's performance at the same time.
            </p>
            <p>
              The interior is fine — nothing fancy, comfortable enough, visibility out the back is basically a joke (you're living by your mirrors), and the rear seat exists mostly as a conversation piece. But none of that matters because you're not buying this car for cargo room. You're buying it because sometimes you need life to feel a little bit alive.
            </p>
            <p>
              Would I rent it again? <strong>Yes. Immediately. Without thinking about it.</strong> Would I want to own one? That's a conversation for another day, but I'll say this — it made my daily feel very boring on the drive back. That's the Camaro effect. It recalibrates you.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="cc-first-review-verdict">
            <div class="cc-first-review-verdict-score">8.5<span>/10</span></div>
            <div class="cc-first-review-verdict-text">
              <p class="cc-first-review-verdict-label">Crystal's Verdict</p>
              <p class="cc-first-review-verdict-quote">"Made me feel like a different person.<br />Would rent again. No hesitation."</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── WHAT I'M DRIVING THIS MONTH ─────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section cc-section-alt" aria-labelledby="driving-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// april 2026</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="driving-heading">What I'm Driving This Month</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">The daily, the next rental target, and the truck I think about way too often.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cc-driving-grid">
        {driving.map((car) => (
          <div class="cc-driving-card">
            <div class="cc-driving-card-thumb" style={car.image ? `background-image: url('${car.image}');` : ''}>
              <span class={`cc-driving-role cc-driving-role-${car.roleClass}`}>{car.role}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cc-driving-card-body">
              <h3 class="cc-driving-name">{car.name}</h3>
              <p class="cc-driving-detail">{car.detail}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── CHEVY GIRL PLAYLIST ─────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section" aria-labelledby="playlist-heading">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// the soundtrack</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="playlist-heading">Chevy Girl Playlist</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">The songs I'm actually listening to. On-brand, no-skip, windows-down certified.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cc-playlist-card">
        <div class="cc-playlist-header">
          <div class="cc-playlist-art">♫</div>
          <div>
            <p class="cc-playlist-title">Chevy Girl Playlist</p>
            <p class="cc-playlist-meta">By Crystal · {playlist.length} songs · ChevyRoots official</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ol class="cc-playlist-tracks">
          {playlist.map((track) => (
            <li class="cc-playlist-track">
              <span class="cc-track-num">{track.num}</span>
              <div class="cc-track-info">
                <p class="cc-track-song">{track.song}</p>
                <p class="cc-track-artist">{track.artist}</p>
              </div>
              <span class="cc-track-vibe">{track.vibe}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── THIS MONTH'S SCHEDULE ───────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section" aria-labelledby="schedule-heading">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// content calendar</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="schedule-heading">This Month's Schedule</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">April is packed. Here's everything I'm covering — reviews, events, and the adventures in between.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cc-cal-grid">
        {schedule.map((item) => (
          <div class={`cc-cal-item ${item.cls === 'live' ? 'cc-cal-live' : ''}`}>
            <span class="cc-cal-date">{item.date}</span>
            <span class="cc-cal-name">{item.name}</span>
            <span class={`cc-cal-status cc-cal-status-${item.cls}`}>{item.status}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── CRYSTAL'S CHEVY RANK ────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section cc-section-alt" aria-labelledby="rank-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// the rankings</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="rank-heading">Crystal's Chevy Rank</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">Every Chevy I get behind the wheel of gets scored. No PR fluff — just honest takes from a girl who actually drives them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cc-rank-grid">
        {rankings.map((item) => (
          <div class={`cc-rank-item ${item.tease ? 'cc-rank-tease' : ''}`}>
            <div>
              <p class="cc-rank-label">{item.label}</p>
              <h3 class="cc-rank-name">{item.name}</h3>
              <p class="cc-rank-quote">{item.quote}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cc-rank-score-wrap">
              <div class="cc-rank-score">{item.score}<span>/10</span></div>
              <div class="cc-rank-bar-wrap">
                <div class="cc-rank-bar" style={`width: ${item.pct}%`}></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── CRYSTAL'S CHEVY WISHLIST ────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section" aria-labelledby="wishlist-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cc-section-header">
        <p class="cc-section-label">// bucket list</p>
        <h2 class="cc-section-title" id="wishlist-heading">Crystal's Chevy Wishlist</h2>
        <p class="cc-section-sub">The Chevys I haven't driven yet but fully intend to. Some have a plan. Some are just dreams right now.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cc-rank-grid">
        {wishlist.map((item) => (
          <div class="cc-rank-item">
            <div>
              <p class="cc-rank-label">{item.label}</p>
              <h3 class="cc-rank-name">{item.name}</h3>
              <p class="cc-rank-quote">{item.quote}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="cc-rank-score-wrap">
              <div class="cc-wishlist-status">{item.status}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cc-divider"><hr /></div>

  {/* ── ASK CRYSTAL ─────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="cc-section" id="ask" aria-labelledby="ask-heading">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="cc-ask-wrap">
        <div class="cc-ask-pitch">
          <p class="cc-section-label">// hit me up</p>
          <h2 class="cc-ask-title" id="ask-heading">Ask<br /><em>Crystal</em></h2>
          <p class="cc-ask-body">Got a Chevy question? Want me to review something? Found a meet I should know about? Drop it here.</p>
          <p class="cc-ask-body">I read everything. I might even make a video about it.</p>
          <div class="cc-ask-note">The best questions end up in content. Just saying.</div>
        </div>
        <form class="cc-form" action="/api/ask-crystal" method="POST">
          <div class="cc-form-row">
            <div class="cc-form-group">
              <label class="cc-form-label" for="ask-name">Name</label>
              <input class="cc-form-input" type="text" id="ask-name" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required />
            </div>
            <div class="cc-form-group">
              <label class="cc-form-label" for="ask-email">Email</label>
              <input class="cc-form-input" type="email" id="ask-email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cc-form-group">
            <label class="cc-form-label" for="ask-question">Your question or request</label>
            <textarea class="cc-form-textarea" id="ask-question" name="question" rows="5" placeholder="Ask me anything Chevy — a model question, a review request, a hot take you need validated..." required></textarea>
          </div>
          <button class="cc-form-btn" type="submit">Send it →</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <NewsletterCTA
    source="crystals-corner-hub"
    heading="Get Crystal's picks in The Weekly Wrench"
    subheading="New Chevy content, event drops, and whatever's on my mind — every Thursday, no filler."
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── HERO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .cc-hero {
    padding: 80px 0;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--charcoal) 0%, #1f1a0e 60%, var(--warm-gray) 100%);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .cc-hero-bg-stripe {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    width: 40%;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, transparent 0%, rgba(196, 160, 53, 0.06) 100%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .cc-hero-gold-bar {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 6px;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--gold);
  }
  .cc-hero-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
    position: relative;
  }
  .cc-hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .cc-hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 10vw, 8rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 0.88;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--off-white);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .cc-hero-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .cc-hero-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .cc-socials {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .cc-social-pill {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(196, 160, 53, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(196, 160, 53, 0.3);
    border-radius: 50px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background var(--transition);
  }
  .cc-social-pill:hover {
    background: rgba(196, 160, 53, 0.15);
  }
  .cc-hero-photo-wrap {
    text-align: center;
  }
  .cc-hero-photo {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    background: var(--warm-gray) url('/photos/crystal/crystal-silverado-zr2-hero.jpg') center / cover no-repeat;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  }
  .cc-hero-photo-caption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--light-gray);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  /* ── SECTION BASE ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .cc-section {
    padding: var(--section-pad) 0;
  }
  .cc-section-alt {
    background: var(--warm-gray);
  }
